As George Zimmerman ramps up his fundraising efforts, those who donate to his cause will be given an unusual piece of memorabilia - his autograph.

Zimmerman, 29, remains in hiding as he awaits trial for fatally shooting 17-year-old Trayvon Martin earlier this year in Sanford, Florida.

The former neighborhood watch leader's attorney said Wednesday that Zimmerman plans to launch the New George Zimmerman Defense Fund next month with a new fund manager that Zimmerman himself will choose.

