Zimmerman has been charged with second-degree murder in the February 26 shooting death of Martin, a Miami teen who was in Sanford visiting his father.

Zimmerman, who was on watch that night, called 911 to report a suspicious man who looked like he was 'up to no good.'

The man was the 17-year-old Martin, who was returning to his father's girlfriend's house from a nearby store where he purchased Skittles for his little brother and an iced tea for himself.

